FT  01 JUL 94 / International Company News: Ferruzzi profits ahead
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP-DJ
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ROME
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Ferruzzi Finanziaria, the Italian food and chemicals group, said operating
profits in the first five months of 1994 were 46.5 per cent higher than
during the same period last year, AP-DJ reports from Rome.
The company said at its annual shareholders meeting that gross operating
margins were 6.8 per cent in the first five months of 1994, compared to
margins of 5 per cent last time.
It said it expected to cut its debt to L11,000bn by the end of 1994,
compared with L21,950bn in 1993. The reduction will come from restructuring
of the debts, capital increases and sales of assets.
Ferruzzi also said gross operating profits for the first two months of 1994
were L447bn, up 26 per cent from the year-ago period.
The restructuring plan has provided total estimated benefits of L800bn so
far, of which L285bn accrues to Montedison, the chemicals group, according
to the company.
