FT  01 JUL 94 / UK Company News: Greenalls to close subsidiary
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JYOTI JEETUN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Greenalls Group, the pubs, drinks and hotel operator, is closing its
Cambrian Soft Drinks subsidiary. The decision will result in a Pounds 4.3m
write down of assets and Pounds 5.5m in redundancy and other costs and the
loss of more than 90 jobs.
Shaw Soft Drinks (Midlands) made an offer for Cambrian, Mr Sudarghara
Dusanj, its managing director, said. Greenalls said, however, Shaw had
failed to come up with a fully financed offer.
Greenalls said it had tried to sell the company but closing Cambrian was
ultimately the best decision for shareholders.
