<HEADLINE>
FT  01 JUL 94 / Observer: Right Charlie
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
It is rare to see anyone - never mind a future king - agree to being grilled
about sexual dalliances on television, the lowest common denominator of
contemporary culture. An instance perhaps, as Lord Byron put it in Don Juan,
of 'Not quite adultery, but adulteration'.
