<HEADLINE>
FT  01 JUL 94 / Observer: Only dregs
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Brazilian dexterity is not limited to the soccer field. The Dart family, the
polystyrene-cup billionaires holding Dollars 1.4bn of old Brazilian bank
loans, who refused to join the giant bank debt restructuring in April, has
sued the Brazilian central bank. They are seeking Dollars 60m of back
interest and accelerated payment of the Dollars 1.4bn.
The Darts are about to find out that their cup runneth not over. In
anticipation of their attitude, the Brazilians ensured the collateral which
backs the debt restructuring was not held - as is traditional - with the New
York Fed. Instead, it was placed with the Bank for International Settlements
in Basle, in the hope of keeping it beyond any court action. Sensible move.
</TEXT>
