   By DAVID WALLER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   FRANKFURT
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Metallgesellschaft, the heavily indebted Frankfurt-based metals, mining and
industrial group, together with its BUS environmental technology subsidiary,
are being sued in New York by Horsehead Resource Development Company.
Horsehead, a US concern 45 per cent owned by BUS, is seeking at least
Dollars 500m in damages. It alleges that BUS and Metallgesellschaft
fraudulently induced Horsehead to enter a joint venture in 1990. Horsehead
claims the German companies misrepresented the quality of their
technologies, failed to market Horsehead's technology in Europe amd
fraudulently concealed the existence of new technology developed by a BUS
affiliate in Europe.
